Trivia

    The only 25-ji, Nightcord de. member who regularly attends school during the day is Mafuyu. While the other members are enrolled in school, Kanade takes her classes online, Ena takes night classes, and Mizuki often skips class.
    The chatting tool 25-ji Nightcord de. use, Nightcord, may be a reference to Discord as they have similar romanizations (ナイトコード and ディスコード respectively).
        Additionally, the layout of Nightcord very closely resembles both the mobile and desktop layouts of Discord. This can be seen in various in-game cards[3] as well as in 25-ji Nightcord de.'s Journey to Bloom animation.
    Wonderlands x Showtime and 25-ji, Nightcord de. are the only two units in which a single person (Tsukasa and Mafuyu) is responsible for the creation of their respective SEKAI. Thus, their SEKAI is filled with things related to them, though it seems that if the owner of the SEKAI allows other people to access their SEKAI, those people can also influence it as well.
    25-ji, Nightcord de is the only unit to have two commissioned songs (Kuyamu to Kaite Mirai and Keitai Renwa) at release date. This is due to, as mentioned by mafumafu in a TwitCasting livestream, after he had finished making Keitai Renwa, Colorful Palette told him it didn't fit the group's sorrowful image.[4]
    The members each have surnames that reference different times of night: Yoisaki ("宵", early night between sunset and midnight), Akiyama ("暁", dawn, specifically just before sunrise), Shinonome ("東雲", dawn, specifically when the sky is bright but the sun is not yet visible), and Asahina ("朝", morning).[5]
